docs.abstract: Capt Ledee (US) charges customs officials at Macapa hijacked his $100,000 liquor cargo bound for Uruguay, held him and his ship until Brazilian Navy capt and US Consul intervened; asks US State Dept help him get compensation; map; Macapa area notorious for smuggling

docs.lead_paragraph: CHICAGO, June 25 (UPI) -- Betsy Rawls slipped to a three-over-par 76 in the women's Western open golf tournament today. As a result, Barbara Romack and Mary Lena Faulk moved into contention, only one stroke behind Miss Rawls, the leader at 225 in the $7,500 event.

headline.main: BETSY RAWLS' LEAD CUT TO ONE STROKE

docs.snippet: BUENOS AIRES, June 25 -- While President Arturo Frondizi travels in Europe receiving official honors and urging investors to put their capital into Argentina, a plan to overthrow the President is being fomented in the army.
docs.lead_paragraph: BUENOS AIRES, June 25 -- While President Arturo Frondizi travels in Europe receiving official honors and urging investors to put their capital into Argentina, a plan to overthrow the President is being fomented in the army.
docs.abstract: plot to overthrow Frondizi being fomented in Army during his Eur tour; Navy and Air Force leaders concerned; Interior Min orders 42 civilians, freed after June 13 plot, rearrested
